What is xpath?
xpath is define as xml path.
it is a syntax or language for finding any element on the web page using XML path expression.
Xpath is used to find the location of any element on web page using HTML dom structure.
Xpath can be used to navigate through elements and attributes in DOM (Document Object Model).

Type of Xpath:
1. Absolute xpath / Full xpath
/html/body/div[6]/div[1]/div[2]/div[2]/form/input
2. Relative xpath / Partial xpath
//input[@id= 'small-searchterms']

Syntax: //tagName[@attribute = 'value']

Diff Between Absolute & Relative xpath
1. Absolute xpath start from root node        | Relative xpath directly jump to element on DOM
2. Absolute xpath start with / (single slash) | Relative xpath start with // (double slash)
3. In Absolute xml we use only tag/nodes      | In Relative xpath we use attributes

Xpath Options
